.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Read `size' bytes into the buffer pointed to by `ptr', from the given
file.
.PP
Returns the number of bytes actually read.
If an error occurs, or the end-of-file is reached, the return value is a
short byte count (or zero).
.PP
